io.github.prolobjectlink.prolog

Interface PrologFloat

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<PrologTerm>, PrologNumber, PrologTerm

    public interface PrologFloat
extends PrologNumber
    Prolog term that represent a single precision floating point number. Extends from PrologNumber who contains an immutable Float instance. The Prolog Provider is the mechanism to create a new Prolog float invoking PrologProvider.newFloat(Number). Two floats numbers are equals if and only if are floats and have equal value. Floats numbers unify only with same value floats or with free variable.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Jose Zalacain
